2461#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_OUT_CONTROL_BUFFER_ADDRESS_LSB _u(0)
2462#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_OUT_CONTROL_BUFFER_ADDRESS_ACCESS "RW"
2463// =============================================================================
2464// Register : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL
2465// Description : Buffer control for both buffers of an endpoint. Fields ending
2466// in a _1 are for buffer 1.
2467// Fields ending in a _0 are for buffer 0. Buffer 1 controls are
2468// only valid if the endpoint is in double buffered mode.
2469#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_OFFSET _u(0x00000080)
2470#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_BITS _u(0xffffffff)
2471#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_RESET _u(0x00000000)
2472// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2473// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1
2474// Description : Buffer 1 is full. For an IN transfer (TX to the host) the bit
2475// is set to indicate the data is valid. For an OUT transfer (RX
2476// from the host) this bit should be left as a 0. The host will
2477// set it when it has filled the buffer with data.
2478#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_RESET _u(0x0)
2479#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_BITS _u(0x80000000)
2480#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_MSB _u(31)
2481#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_LSB _u(31)
2482#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_ACCESS "RW"
2483// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2484// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1
2485// Description : Buffer 1 is the last buffer of the transfer.
2486#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_RESET _u(0x0)
2487#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_BITS _u(0x40000000)
2488#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_MSB _u(30)
2489#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_LSB _u(30)
2490#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_ACCESS "RW"
2491// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2492// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_PID_1
2493// Description : The data pid of buffer 1.
2494#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_PID_1_RESET _u(0x0)
2495#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_PID_1_BITS _u(0x20000000)
2496#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_PID_1_MSB _u(29)
2497#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_PID_1_LSB _u(29)
2498#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_PID_1_ACCESS "RW"
2499// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2500// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET
2501// Description : The number of bytes buffer 1 is offset from buffer 0 in
2502// Isochronous mode. Only valid in double buffered mode for an
2503// Isochronous endpoint.
2504// For a non Isochronous endpoint the offset is always 64 bytes.
2505// 0x0 -> 128
2506// 0x1 -> 256
2507// 0x2 -> 512
2508// 0x3 -> 1024
2509#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_RESET _u(0x0)
2510#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_BITS _u(0x18000000)

2512#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_LSB _u(27)
2513#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_ACCESS "RW"
2514#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_128 _u(0x0)
2515#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_256 _u(0x1)
2516#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_512 _u(0x2)
2517#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_1024 _u(0x3)
2518// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2519// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP0_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_AVAILABLE_1
2520// Description : Buffer 1 is available. This bit is set to indicate the buffer
2521// can be used by the controller. The controller clears the
2522// available bit when writing the status back.

2768// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP1_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET
2769// Description : The number of bytes buffer 1 is offset from buffer 0 in

2771// Isochronous endpoint.

2773// 0x0 -> 128
2774// 0x1 -> 256
2775// 0x2 -> 512
2776// 0x3 -> 1024

2783#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP1_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_256 _u(0x1)
2784#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP1_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_512 _u(0x2)
2785#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP1_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_1024 _u(0x3)

3402// Register : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP3_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL

4340// Register : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP7_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL
4341// Description : Buffer control for both buffers of an endpoint. Fields ending
4342// in a _1 are for buffer 1.
4343// Fields ending in a _0 are for buffer 0. Buffer 1 controls are
4344// only valid if the endpoint is in double buffered mode.

4348// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
4349// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP7_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1
4350// Description : Buffer 1 is full. For an IN transfer (TX to the host) the bit
4351// is set to indicate the data is valid. For an OUT transfer (RX
4352// from the host) this bit should be left as a 0. The host will
4353// set it when it has filled the buffer with data.
4354#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP7_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_RESET _u(0x0)
4355#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP7_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_BITS _u(0x80000000)
4356#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP7_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_MSB _u(31)

4608// Register : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL
4609// Description : Buffer control for both buffers of an endpoint. Fields ending
4610// in a _1 are for buffer 1.
4611// Fields ending in a _0 are for buffer 0. Buffer 1 controls are
4612// only valid if the endpoint is in double buffered mode.
4613#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_OFFSET _u(0x000000c0)
4614#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_BITS _u(0xffffffff)

4616// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
4617// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1
4618// Description : Buffer 1 is full. For an IN transfer (TX to the host) the bit
4619// is set to indicate the data is valid. For an OUT transfer (RX
4620// from the host) this bit should be left as a 0. The host will
4621// set it when it has filled the buffer with data.
4622#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_RESET _u(0x0)
4623#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_BITS _u(0x80000000)
4624#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_MSB _u(31)

4631#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_BITS _u(0x40000000)

4643// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
4644// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP8_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET

5545// =============================================================================
5546// Register : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP11_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL
5547// Description : Buffer control for both buffers of an endpoint. Fields ending
5548// in a _1 are for buffer 1.
5549// Fields ending in a _0 are for buffer 0. Buffer 1 controls are
5550// only valid if the endpoint is in double buffered mode.

5552#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP11_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_BITS _u(0xffffffff)

5554// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5555// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP11_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1
5556// Description : Buffer 1 is full. For an IN transfer (TX to the host) the bit

5558// from the host) this bit should be left as a 0. The host will
5559// set it when it has filled the buffer with data.

5561#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP11_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_BITS _u(0x80000000)

5569#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP11_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_BITS _u(0x40000000)

5856// 0x1 -> 256
5857// 0x2 -> 512

5866#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP12_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_512 _u(0x2)

6453#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_RESET_BITS _u(0x00001000)
6454#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_RESET_MSB _u(12)
6455#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_RESET_LSB _u(12)
6456#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_RESET_ACCESS "RW"
6457// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6458// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_STALL
6459// Description : Reply with a stall (valid for both buffers).
6460#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_STALL_RESET _u(0x0)
6461#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_STALL_BITS _u(0x00000800)
6462#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_STALL_MSB _u(11)
6463#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_STALL_LSB _u(11)
6464#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_STALL_ACCESS "RW"
6465// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6466// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_AVAILABLE_0
6467// Description : Buffer 0 is available. This bit is set to indicate the buffer
6468// can be used by the controller. The controller clears the
6469// available bit when writing the status back.
6470#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_AVAILABLE_0_RESET _u(0x0)
6471#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_AVAILABLE_0_BITS _u(0x00000400)
6472#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_AVAILABLE_0_MSB _u(10)
6473#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_AVAILABLE_0_LSB _u(10)
6474#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_AVAILABLE_0_ACCESS "RW"

6477// Description : The length of the data in buffer 0.
6478#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_LENGTH_0_RESET _u(0x000)
6479#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP14_OUT_BUFFER_CONTROL_LENGTH_0_BITS _u(0x000003ff)

6483// =============================================================================
6484// Register : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL
6485// Description : Buffer control for both buffers of an endpoint. Fields ending
6486// in a _1 are for buffer 1.
6487// Fields ending in a _0 are for buffer 0. Buffer 1 controls are
6488// only valid if the endpoint is in double buffered mode.
6489#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_OFFSET _u(0x000000f8)
6490#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_BITS _u(0xffffffff)
6491#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_RESET _u(0x00000000)
6492// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6493// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1
6494// Description : Buffer 1 is full. For an IN transfer (TX to the host) the bit
6495// is set to indicate the data is valid. For an OUT transfer (RX
6496// from the host) this bit should be left as a 0. The host will
6497// set it when it has filled the buffer with data.
6498#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_RESET _u(0x0)
6499#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_BITS _u(0x80000000)
6500#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_MSB _u(31)
6501#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_LSB _u(31)
6502#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_FULL_1_ACCESS "RW"
6503// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6504// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1
6505// Description : Buffer 1 is the last buffer of the transfer.
6506#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_RESET _u(0x0)
6507#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_BITS _u(0x40000000)
6508#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_LAST_1_MSB _u(30)

6520// Field : USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET

6535#define USB_DEVICE_DPRAM_EP15_IN_BUFFER_CONTROL_DOUBLE_BUFFER_ISO_OFFSET_VALUE_256 _u(0x1)
